<!-- Q1 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Rank-Nullity - Theorem Statement</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>For a linear map \(T:V\to W\) with \(\dim V=n<\infty\), the rank–nullity theorem states:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(\mathrm{rank}(T)+\mathrm{nullity}(T)=n\)</strong></p><p>The rank–nullity (dimension) theorem: \(\dim(\mathrm{Im}\,T)+\dim(\ker T)=\dim V\). It is fundamental and implies: \(T\) injective (\(\ker T=0\)) + \(\dim V=\dim W\) \(\Rightarrow\) \(T\) is an isomorphism. The proof uses a basis for \(\ker T\), extends it to a basis for \(V\), and shows the images of the extending vectors form a basis for \(\mathrm{Im}\,T\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\mathrm{rank}(T)=\mathrm{nullity}(T)\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\mathrm{rank}(T)+\mathrm{nullity}(T)=\dim V\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\mathrm{rank}(T)\cdot\mathrm{nullity}(T)=\dim V\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\mathrm{rank}(T)=\dim W\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q2 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Rank - 3x3 Matrix Row Reduction</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The rank of \(A=\begin{pmatrix}1&2&3\\2&4&6\\3&6&9\end{pmatrix}\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) 1</strong></p><p>Row 2 = 2×Row 1, Row 3 = 3×Row 1. All rows are multiples of the first, so only 1 independent row. Rank = 1. Nullity = 3−1 = 2. The null space is 2-dimensional, spanned by \((-2,1,0)^T\) and \((-3,0,1)^T\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
