<!-- Q5 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Rank - Full Rank Matrix</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>An \(m\times n\) matrix \(A\) with \(m<n\) can have at most rank:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) \(m\)</strong></p><p>The rank of a matrix is at most \(\min(m,n)\). With \(m<n\) (more columns than rows), the maximum rank is \(m\). A matrix achieving this is called "full row rank" — its rows are linearly independent. Full row rank \(\Rightarrow T\) is surjective.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
