<!-- Q8 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Rank - Rank of Outer Product</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>If \(u,v\in\mathbb{R}^n\) are nonzero vectors, the rank of the outer product matrix \(A=uv^T\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) 1</strong></p><p>Every column of \(uv^T\) is a scalar multiple of \(u\): column \(j = v_j u\). So the column space is spanned by \(u\), which is 1-dimensional. Rank = 1. Nullity = n−1. This is the prototype of a rank-1 update in numerical linear algebra.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
