<!-- Q9 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Rank - Sylvester Inequality</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Sylvester's inequality states: for \(A\) (\(m\times n\)) and \(B\) (\(n\times p\)):  \(\mathrm{rank}(A)+\mathrm{rank}(B)-n\leq\mathrm{rank}(AB)\leq\):</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(\min(\mathrm{rank}(A),\mathrm{rank}(B))\)</strong></p><p>Sylvester: \(\mathrm{rank}(A)+\mathrm{rank}(B)-n\leq\mathrm{rank}(AB)\leq\min(\mathrm{rank}(A),\mathrm{rank}(B))\). The lower bound says how much rank can be "lost"; the upper bound is the general product inequality. Together they give precise control over rank of a product.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
